**Describe your issue**

I just upgraded from Tailwind 3 and my custom extractor in `tailwind.config.js` no longer works, it is not called at all:

```js
export default {
    content: {
        files: ["../myproject/**/*.kt"],
        extract: {
            kt: (content) => {
                console.log("Extracting classes from kt file...");
                return content.match(/classes\s*=\s*"([^"]*)"/g) || [];
            }
        }
    },
    theme: {
        extend: {},
    },
    plugins: [],
}
```

If I downgrade to Tailwind 3 I can see the console log statements when I run my build. If I upgrade to Tailwind 4 I don't, so either this feature was removed or it works in some other way.

Fixes #18678

When given a simple plugin like this:
```js
export default {
  content: [{ raw: '!a' },],
  plugins: [
    ({ addBase }) => addBase({
      '@media (min-width: 1728px)': {
        '.a': { 'padding-top': '1rem !important' },
        '.b': { 'padding-right': '1rem !important' },
      }
    }),
  ],
}
```

If this plugin saw the utility `!a` it would correctly modify both rules to eliminate any irrelevant classes. Unfortunately, in the case of the 2nd rule this meant it's left with an empty selector which is invalid.

We now detect this case and remove the rule if that happens.
